&lt;p&gt;WITHIN is hiring 8 creatives into an 8-week paid fellowship designed to be the highest-leverage 8 weeks of your career so far.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most performance creative jobs treat the work as the lesser cousin of brand — the grind you do until you can get into a brand shop. We don&#39;t. Performance creative done well is a real craft, and we hire people who already know that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here&#39;s why this is different from every other job you&#39;ve looked at:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;More reps than anywhere else.&lt;/strong&gt; You&#39;ll write more scripts, ship more hooks, see more of your work go live in your first 8 weeks at WITHIN than a brand creative gets in their first year somewhere else. Reps are how taste develops. The data tells you within 48 hours whether you nailed it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direct access.&lt;/strong&gt; For your first 8 weeks, you&#39;re on Quinn&#39;s team — our Head of Creative. Working on 2-3 live client accounts. Pitching new business. Owning work, not shadowing it. At most shops your level, you&#39;d be three layers down.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The work mix is 70% performance creative + 30% campaign development and rebrands&lt;/strong&gt; for brands you&#39;d recognize. The 30% is a real perk — but it&#39;s not the reason to take this job. If you don&#39;t already think performance creative is interesting in itself, please apply somewhere else.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At week 8, fellows who&#39;ve shown they can own work at our velocity&lt;/strong&gt; move into the broader creative team under one of our Creative Directors as full-time Creative Leads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for three things we can&#39;t train:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;hustle, taste, and curiosity&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Who you are&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve made something real. Maybe a TikTok account that grew past 5K followers because the content was actually good. Maybe a Substack. Maybe a spec campaign for a brand you love that they never asked for. The work is public and shows your taste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can write a hook in 90 seconds that makes someone stop scrolling — and you can articulate why it works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You think performance creative is interesting in itself.&lt;/strong&gt; You&#39;ve thought about hooks, fatigue, iteration, platform mechanics. You read ad teardowns. You watch ads and have opinions about what&#39;s working before you check the metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re already using AI tools in your creative workflow. Midjourney, Runway, Sora, ElevenLabs, Veo, whichever — and you have strong opinions about which are real and which are hype.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Either you&#39;re a recent grad of a portfolio or design program (Brandcenter, Miami Ad School, SVA, FIT, Parsons, Pratt, Newhouse, RISD, equivalent) OR you&#39;ve spent the last 1–3 years building an audience and learning to make things people stop for.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You live in NYC or you&#39;re moving for this. This fellowship is in person.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Who you are not&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&quot;I need to ramp up before I can ship work.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Looking for a senior title and a quiet corner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You think performance creative is what you do to pay the bills until you can do &quot;real creative.&quot;&lt;/strong&gt; The 30% brand work isn&#39;t going to be enough to keep you happy if you don&#39;t already love the 70%.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portfolio is beautiful posters with no brand attached, no audience, no result.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitch concepts daily. Ship work weekly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write scripts, draft storyboards, set design direction across video, static, and AI-generated formats.&

